{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2183,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":5105,"text":"I moved to America 12 years ago\nwith my wife Terry and our two kids."},{"time":9530,"text":"Actually, truthfully, we moved\nto Los Angeles --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":12340,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":15788,"text":"thinking we were moving\nto America, but anyway --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18146,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20827,"text":"It's a short plane ride\nfrom Los Angeles to America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25109,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27304,"text":"I got here 12 years ago,"},{"time":29059,"text":"and when I got here,\nI was told various things,"},{"time":32869,"text":"like, \"Americans don't get irony.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":36628,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38792,"text":"Have you come across this idea?"},{"time":41038,"text":"It's not true."},{"time":42221,"text":"I've traveled the whole length\nand breadth of this country."},{"time":45007,"text":"I have found no evidence\nthat Americans don't get irony."},{"time":47657,"text":"It's one of those cultural myths,"},{"time":50258,"text":"like, \"The British are reserved.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":52480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":54393,"text":"I don't know why people think this."},{"time":56455,"text":"We've invaded every country\nwe've encountered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58966,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62818,"text":"But it's not true Americans\ndon't get irony,"},{"time":65126,"text":"but I just want you to know\nthat that's what people"},{"time":67622,"text":"are saying about you behind your back."},{"time":69456,"text":"You know, so when you leave\nliving rooms in Europe,"},{"time":72416,"text":"people say, thankfully,\nnobody was ironic in your presence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75647,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":77058,"text":"But I knew that Americans get irony"},{"time":79619,"text":"when I came across that legislation,\n\"No Child Left Behind.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":83368,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85174,"text":"Because whoever thought\nof that title gets irony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88799,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90561,"text":"Don't they?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92043,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97866,"text":"Because it's leaving\nmillions of children behind."},{"time":101413,"text":"Now I can see that's not a very attractive\nname for legislation:"},{"time":104749,"text":"\"Millions of Children Left Behind.\""},{"time":106495,"text":"I can see that."},{"time":108264,"text":"What's the plan?"},{"time":109485,"text":"We propose to leave\nmillions of children behind,"},{"time":112273,"text":"and here's how it's going to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114035,"text":"And it's working beautifully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115445,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116476,"text":"In some parts of the country,"},{"time":117881,"text":"60 percent of kids drop out\nof high school."},{"time":121677,"text":"In the Native American communities,"},{"time":123368,"text":"it's 80 percent of kids."},{"time":125777,"text":"If we halved that number,"},{"time":128368,"text":"one estimate is it would create\na net gain to the U.S. economy"},{"time":134050,"text":"over 10 years,\nof nearly a trillion dollars."},{"time":139280,"text":"From an economic point of view,"},{"time":140857,"text":"this is good math, isn't it,\nthat we should do this?"},{"time":143789,"text":"It actually costs an enormous amount"},{"time":146138,"text":"to mop up the damage\nfrom the dropout crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150300,"text":"But the dropout crisis\nis just the tip of an iceberg."},{"time":154029,"text":"What it doesn't count\nare all the kids who are in school"},{"time":156720,"text":"but being disengaged\nfrom it, who don't enjoy it,"},{"time":160282,"text":"who don't get any real benefit from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163622,"text":"And the reason is not\nthat we're not spending enough money."},{"time":166614,"text":"America spends more money on education\nthan most other countries."},{"time":170103,"text":"Class sizes are smaller\nthan in many countries."},{"time":173681,"text":"And there are hundreds\nof initiatives every year"},{"time":175967,"text":"to try and improve education."},{"time":178244,"text":"The trouble is, it's all going\nin the wrong direction."},{"time":182765,"text":"There are three principles\non which human life flourishes,"},{"time":187364,"text":"and they are contradicted\nby the culture of education"},{"time":191375,"text":"under which most teachers have to labor"},{"time":193652,"text":"and most students have to endure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197207,"text":"The first is this, that human beings\nare naturally different and diverse."},{"time":204387,"text":"Can I ask you, how many of you\nhave got children of your own?"},{"time":208892,"text":"Okay. Or grandchildren."},{"time":211905,"text":"How about two children or more? Right."},{"time":215645,"text":"And the rest of you\nhave seen such children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217765,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220525,"text":"Small people wandering about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222039,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223785,"text":"I will make you a bet,"},{"time":225636,"text":"and I am confident\nthat I will win the bet."},{"time":227708,"text":"If you've got two children or more,"},{"time":229551,"text":"I bet you they are completely\ndifferent from each other."},{"time":233380,"text":"Aren't they?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":235825,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237751,"text":"You would never confuse them, would you?"},{"time":240354,"text":"Like, \"Which one are you? Remind me.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":242418,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":245252,"text":"\"Your mother and I need\nsome color-coding system"},{"time":247689,"text":"so we don't get confused.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":250052,"text":"Education under \"No Child Left Behind\""},{"time":252995,"text":"is based on not diversity but conformity."},{"time":257818,"text":"What schools are encouraged\nto do is to find out"},{"time":260376,"text":"what kids can do across\na very narrow spectrum of achievement."},{"time":264736,"text":"One of the effects\nof \"No Child Left Behind\""},{"time":267428,"text":"has been to narrow the focus\nonto the so-called STEM disciplines."},{"time":271201,"text":"They're very important."},{"time":272835,"text":"I'm not here to argue\nagainst science and math."},{"time":275098,"text":"On the contrary, they're necessary\nbut they're not sufficient."},{"time":279178,"text":"A real education has to give equal weight"},{"time":281377,"text":"to the arts, the humanities,\nto physical education."},{"time":285114,"text":"An awful lot of kids, sorry, thank you --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287562,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":292688,"text":"One estimate in America currently\nis that something like 10 percent of kids,"},{"time":296575,"text":"getting on that way,"},{"time":298090,"text":"are being diagnosed\nwith various conditions"},{"time":302180,"text":"under the broad title\nof attention deficit disorder."},{"time":306502,"text":"ADHD."},{"time":308234,"text":"I'm not saying there's no such thing."},{"time":310699,"text":"I just don't believe\nit's an epidemic like this."},{"time":313154,"text":"If you sit kids down, hour after hour,"},{"time":315970,"text":"doing low-grade clerical work,"},{"time":319306,"text":"don't be surprised if they start\nto fidget, you know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":322435,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":323887,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":330089,"text":"Children are not, for the most part,\nsuffering from a psychological condition."},{"time":334248,"text":"They're suffering from childhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336261,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340379,"text":"And I know this because\nI spent my early life as a child."},{"time":343311,"text":"I went through the whole thing."},{"time":346705,"text":"Kids prosper best with a broad curriculum\nthat celebrates their various talents,"},{"time":351723,"text":"not just a small range of them."},{"time":353360,"text":"And by the way, the arts\naren't just important"},{"time":355583,"text":"because they improve math scores."},{"time":357217,"text":"They're important because they speak\nto parts of children's being"},{"time":360358,"text":"which are otherwise untouched."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362312,"text":"The second, thank you --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":364144,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368562,"text":"The second principle\nthat drives human life flourishing"},{"time":372725,"text":"is curiosity."},{"time":374512,"text":"If you can light the spark\nof curiosity in a child,"},{"time":377900,"text":"they will learn without any further\nassistance, very often."},{"time":381563,"text":"Children are natural learners."},{"time":383548,"text":"It's a real achievement\nto put that particular ability out,"},{"time":387864,"text":"or to stifle it."},{"time":390155,"text":"Curiosity is the engine of achievement."},{"time":394392,"text":"Now the reason I say this"},{"time":395769,"text":"is because one of the effects\nof the current culture here,"},{"time":399968,"text":"if I can say so,"},{"time":401194,"text":"has been to de-professionalize teachers."},{"time":404876,"text":"There is no system in the world\nor any school in the country"},{"time":410212,"text":"that is better than its teachers."},{"time":413028,"text":"Teachers are the lifeblood\nof the success of schools."},{"time":417723,"text":"But teaching is a creative profession."},{"time":420814,"text":"Teaching, properly conceived,\nis not a delivery system."},{"time":424174,"text":"You know, you're not there just\nto pass on received information."},{"time":427246,"text":"Great teachers do that,"},{"time":429498,"text":"but what great teachers also do is mentor,"},{"time":432567,"text":"stimulate, provoke, engage."},{"time":435936,"text":"You see, in the end,\neducation is about learning."},{"time":438881,"text":"If there's no learning going on,\nthere's no education going on."},{"time":441995,"text":"And people can spend an awful lot of time"},{"time":443992,"text":"discussing education\nwithout ever discussing learning."},{"time":446589,"text":"The whole point of education\nis to get people to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449186,"text":"An old friend of mine --\nactually very old, he's dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452976,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":455672,"text":"That's as old as it gets, I'm afraid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458173,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":461960,"text":"But a wonderful guy he was,\nwonderful philosopher."},{"time":466737,"text":"He used to talk about the difference"},{"time":469036,"text":"between the task\nand achievement senses of verbs."},{"time":473818,"text":"You can be engaged\nin the activity of something,"},{"time":476165,"text":"but not really be\nachieving it, like dieting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479086,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":480111,"text":"It's a very good example."},{"time":481865,"text":"There he is. He's dieting."},{"time":483236,"text":"Is he losing any weight? Not really."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485129,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486745,"text":"Teaching is a word like that."},{"time":488236,"text":"You can say, \"There's Deborah,\nshe's in room 34, she's teaching.\""},{"time":491902,"text":"But if nobody's learning anything,"},{"time":493775,"text":"she may be engaged in the task of teaching\nbut not actually fulfilling it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498419,"text":"The role of a teacher\nis to facilitate learning."},{"time":501408,"text":"That's it."},{"time":502679,"text":"And part of the problem is, I think,"},{"time":504579,"text":"that the dominant culture\nof education has come to focus"},{"time":508035,"text":"on not teaching and learning, but testing."},{"time":511884,"text":"Now, testing is important."},{"time":513485,"text":"Standardized tests have a place."},{"time":515798,"text":"But they should not be\nthe dominant culture of education."},{"time":518715,"text":"They should be diagnostic.\nThey should help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520835,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528247,"text":"If I go for a medical examination,\nI want some standardized tests."},{"time":533162,"text":"I do."},{"time":534387,"text":"I want to know\nwhat my cholesterol level is"},{"time":536498,"text":"compared to everybody else's\non a standard scale."},{"time":538879,"text":"I don't want to be told on some scale\nmy doctor invented in the car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542145,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":544246,"text":"\"Your cholesterol\nis what I call Level Orange.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":546493,"text":"\"Really?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":547700,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":549501,"text":"\"Is that good?\" \"We don't know.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":551168,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552746,"text":"But all that should support learning."},{"time":555336,"text":"It shouldn't obstruct it,\nwhich of course it often does."},{"time":559275,"text":"So in place of curiosity,\nwhat we have is a culture of compliance."},{"time":563975,"text":"Our children and teachers are encouraged\nto follow routine algorithms"},{"time":569499,"text":"rather than to excite that power\nof imagination and curiosity."},{"time":574060,"text":"And the third principle is this:\nthat human life is inherently creative."},{"time":578065,"text":"It's why we all have different résumés."},{"time":580453,"text":"We create our lives,"},{"time":582094,"text":"and we can recreate them\nas we go through them."},{"time":584697,"text":"It's the common currency\nof being a human being."},{"time":587302,"text":"It's why human culture\nis so interesting and diverse and dynamic."},{"time":591469,"text":"I mean, other animals may well have\nimaginations and creativity,"},{"time":595330,"text":"but it's not so much\nin evidence, is it, as ours?"},{"time":598062,"text":"I mean, you may have a dog."},{"time":600780,"text":"And your dog may get depressed."},{"time":603644,"text":"You know, but it doesn't listen\nto Radiohead, does it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":606240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":610019,"text":"And sit staring out the window\nwith a bottle of Jack Daniels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612948,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617145,"text":"\"Would you like to come for a walk?\""},{"time":618971,"text":"\"No, I'm fine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":620196,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621954,"text":"\"You go. I'll wait. But take pictures.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":625795,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":627660,"text":"We all create our own lives\nthrough this restless process"},{"time":630433,"text":"of imagining alternatives\nand possibilities,"},{"time":632553,"text":"and one of the roles of education"},{"time":635019,"text":"is to awaken and develop\nthese powers of creativity."},{"time":638717,"text":"Instead, what we have\nis a culture of standardization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642417,"text":"Now, it doesn't have to be that way."},{"time":644663,"text":"It really doesn't."},{"time":646637,"text":"Finland regularly comes out on top\nin math, science and reading."},{"time":651341,"text":"Now, we only know\nthat's what they do well at,"},{"time":653635,"text":"because that's all that's being tested."},{"time":655791,"text":"That's one of the problems of the test."},{"time":657673,"text":"They don't look for other things\nthat matter just as much."},{"time":660752,"text":"The thing about work in Finland is this:"},{"time":664102,"text":"they don't obsess about those disciplines."},{"time":666474,"text":"They have a very broad\napproach to education,"},{"time":668594,"text":"which includes humanities,\nphysical education, the arts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673064,"text":"Second, there is no standardized\ntesting in Finland."},{"time":678511,"text":"I mean, there's a bit,"},{"time":680152,"text":"but it's not what gets\npeople up in the morning,"},{"time":682462,"text":"what keeps them at their desks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684342,"text":"The third thing --\nand I was at a meeting recently"},{"time":686722,"text":"with some people from Finland,\nactual Finnish people,"},{"time":689287,"text":"and somebody from the American system\nwas saying to the people in Finland,"},{"time":694183,"text":"\"What do you do\nabout the drop-out rate in Finland?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":697782,"text":"And they all looked a bit\nbemused, and said,"},{"time":700212,"text":"\"Well, we don't have one."},{"time":702522,"text":"Why would you drop out?"},{"time":704591,"text":"If people are in trouble,\nwe get to them quite quickly"},{"time":707165,"text":"and we help and support them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":708657,"text":"Now people always say,"},{"time":710248,"text":"\"Well, you know, you can't compare\nFinland to America.\""},{"time":713463,"text":"No. I think there's a population\nof around five million in Finland."},{"time":717230,"text":"But you can compare it\nto a state in America."},{"time":720815,"text":"Many states in America\nhave fewer people in them than that."},{"time":724719,"text":"I mean, I've been\nto some states in America"},{"time":726791,"text":"and I was the only person there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728372,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":730199,"text":"Really. Really."},{"time":732824,"text":"I was asked to lock up when I left."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734802,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738897,"text":"But what all the high-performing\nsystems in the world do"},{"time":742830,"text":"is currently what is not evident, sadly,"},{"time":746718,"text":"across the systems in America --"},{"time":748983,"text":"I mean, as a whole."},{"time":750703,"text":"One is this:"},{"time":752036,"text":"they individualize teaching and learning."},{"time":755797,"text":"They recognize that it's students\nwho are learning"},{"time":759454,"text":"and the system has to engage them,"},{"time":761610,"text":"their curiosity, their individuality,\nand their creativity."},{"time":765305,"text":"That's how you get them to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767570,"text":"The second is that they attribute\na very high status"},{"time":771784,"text":"to the teaching profession."},{"time":774353,"text":"They recognize\nthat you can't improve education"},{"time":777009,"text":"if you don't pick great people to teach\nand keep giving them"},{"time":780002,"text":"constant support\nand professional development."},{"time":782501,"text":"Investing in professional\ndevelopment is not a cost."},{"time":785219,"text":"It's an investment,"},{"time":786832,"text":"and every other country\nthat's succeeding well knows that,"},{"time":789601,"text":"whether it's Australia, Canada,"},{"time":792055,"text":"South Korea, Singapore,\nHong Kong or Shanghai."},{"time":796506,"text":"They know that to be the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798195,"text":"And the third is,"},{"time":799585,"text":"they devolve responsibility\nto the school level"},{"time":803339,"text":"for getting the job done."},{"time":805243,"text":"You see, there's a big difference here"},{"time":807372,"text":"between going into a mode of command\nand control in education --"},{"time":811385,"text":"That's what happens in some systems."},{"time":813137,"text":"Central or state governments decide,"},{"time":815760,"text":"they know best and they're going\nto tell you what to do."},{"time":818799,"text":"The trouble is that education\ndoesn't go on"},{"time":822318,"text":"in the committee rooms\nof our legislative buildings."},{"time":825250,"text":"It happens in classrooms and schools,"},{"time":828284,"text":"and the people who do it\nare the teachers and the students,"},{"time":831357,"text":"and if you remove their discretion,\nit stops working."},{"time":835117,"text":"You have to put it back to the people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837815,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":842991,"text":"There is wonderful work\nhappening in this country."},{"time":845918,"text":"But I have to say it's happening"},{"time":847499,"text":"in spite of the dominant\nculture of education,"},{"time":850065,"text":"not because of it."},{"time":851466,"text":"It's like people are sailing\ninto a headwind all the time."},{"time":855070,"text":"And the reason I think is this:"},{"time":857732,"text":"that many of the current policies"},{"time":859764,"text":"are based on mechanistic\nconceptions of education."},{"time":863909,"text":"It's like education\nis an industrial process"},{"time":867677,"text":"that can be improved\njust by having better data,"},{"time":870684,"text":"and somewhere in the back of the mind\nof some policy makers"},{"time":873624,"text":"is this idea that if we fine-tune it\nwell enough, if we just get it right,"},{"time":877758,"text":"it will all hum along perfectly\ninto the future."},{"time":880576,"text":"It won't, and it never did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883805,"text":"The point is that education\nis not a mechanical system."},{"time":887756,"text":"It's a human system."},{"time":889927,"text":"It's about people,"},{"time":891880,"text":"people who either do want\nto learn or don't want to learn."},{"time":894708,"text":"Every student who drops\nout of school has a reason for it"},{"time":899523,"text":"which is rooted in their own biography."},{"time":901844,"text":"They may find it boring."},{"time":903446,"text":"They may find it irrelevant."},{"time":905166,"text":"They may find that it's at odds with\nthe life they're living outside of school."},{"time":910286,"text":"There are trends,\nbut the stories are always unique."},{"time":914087,"text":"I was at a meeting recently\nin Los Angeles of --"},{"time":916765,"text":"they're called alternative\neducation programs."},{"time":919224,"text":"These are programs designed\nto get kids back into education."},{"time":922552,"text":"They have certain common features."},{"time":924357,"text":"They're very personalized."},{"time":926548,"text":"They have strong support for the teachers,"},{"time":929984,"text":"close links with the community\nand a broad and diverse curriculum,"},{"time":933551,"text":"and often programs which involve students\noutside school as well as inside school."},{"time":938790,"text":"And they work."},{"time":940674,"text":"What's interesting to me is,\nthese are called \"alternative education.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":944371,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":945443,"text":"You know?"},{"time":947714,"text":"And all the evidence\nfrom around the world is,"},{"time":949933,"text":"if we all did that, there'd be\nno need for the alternative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953406,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":961135,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":962160,"text":"So I think we have to embrace\na different metaphor."},{"time":964664,"text":"We have to recognize\nthat it's a human system,"},{"time":967197,"text":"and there are conditions\nunder which people thrive,"},{"time":971077,"text":"and conditions under which they don't."},{"time":973698,"text":"We are after all organic creatures,"},{"time":976969,"text":"and the culture of the school\nis absolutely essential."},{"time":981269,"text":"Culture is an organic term, isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":983937,"text":"Not far from where I live\nis a place called Death Valley."},{"time":987627,"text":"Death Valley is the hottest,\ndriest place in America,"},{"time":993291,"text":"and nothing grows there."},{"time":996219,"text":"Nothing grows there\nbecause it doesn't rain."},{"time":998664,"text":"Hence, Death Valley."},{"time":1000917,"text":"In the winter of 2004,\nit rained in Death Valley."},{"time":1008064,"text":"Seven inches of rain fell\nover a very short period."},{"time":1012010,"text":"And in the spring of 2005,\nthere was a phenomenon."},{"time":1017038,"text":"The whole floor of Death Valley\nwas carpeted in flowers for a while."},{"time":1023664,"text":"What it proved is this:"},{"time":1025450,"text":"that Death Valley isn't dead."},{"time":1029424,"text":"It's dormant."},{"time":1031569,"text":"Right beneath the surface\nare these seeds of possibility"},{"time":1035051,"text":"waiting for the right conditions\nto come about,"},{"time":1038613,"text":"and with organic systems,\nif the conditions are right,"},{"time":1042099,"text":"life is inevitable."},{"time":1044290,"text":"It happens all the time."},{"time":1045685,"text":"You take an area, a school, a district,"},{"time":1048270,"text":"you change the conditions, give people\na different sense of possibility,"},{"time":1051698,"text":"a different set of expectations,\na broader range of opportunities,"},{"time":1054840,"text":"you cherish and value the relationships\nbetween teachers and learners,"},{"time":1058150,"text":"you offer people\nthe discretion to be creative"},{"time":1060365,"text":"and to innovate in what they do,"},{"time":1062208,"text":"and schools that were once\nbereft spring to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1065669,"text":"Great leaders know that."},{"time":1067662,"text":"The real role of leadership\nin education --"},{"time":1069787,"text":"and I think it's true\nat the national level,"},{"time":1071908,"text":"the state level, at the school level --"},{"time":1073902,"text":"is not and should not be\ncommand and control."},{"time":1078302,"text":"The real role of leadership\nis climate control,"},{"time":1082549,"text":"creating a climate of possibility."},{"time":1084852,"text":"And if you do that, people will rise to it"},{"time":1087306,"text":"and achieve things\nthat you completely did not anticipate"},{"time":1090539,"text":"and couldn't have expected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1092506,"text":"There's a wonderful quote\nfrom Benjamin Franklin."},{"time":1094883,"text":"\"There are three sorts\nof people in the world:"},{"time":1097486,"text":"Those who are immovable,"},{"time":1100026,"text":"people who don't get it,"},{"time":1101273,"text":"or don't want to do anything about it;"},{"time":1103168,"text":"there are people who are movable,"},{"time":1104904,"text":"people who see the need for change"},{"time":1106548,"text":"and are prepared to listen to it;"},{"time":1108872,"text":"and there are people who move,"},{"time":1110723,"text":"people who make things happen.\""},{"time":1112796,"text":"And if we can encourage more people,\nthat will be a movement."},{"time":1117339,"text":"And if the movement is strong enough,"},{"time":1119526,"text":"that's, in the best sense\nof the word, a revolution."},{"time":1122866,"text":"And that's what we need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124447,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1125680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1129569,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130819,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}